  "text": "Even though the softmax Bellman operator was shown in [CITATION_1] not to be a contraction, with a counterexample, we are not aware of any prior work showing the performance bound by using the softmax Bellman operator in Q-iteration. Furthermore, it is interesting to investigate how fast T soft approaches T , given the fact that T soft → T when τ → ∞. We propose to answer these questions in Section 3.1. We also show in Section 3.2 how the softmax Bellman operator can reduce the overestimation bias and gradient noise, given certain assumptions.",
